The moment has come to demolish our bedroom. The last room of the house where nothing has been done yet, just a bit of decoration.
Remove the awful electric fireplace and the mantle. Frame the chimney, replace the damaged plaster and sand it. Make a custom closet.
We always start with a quick pencil sketch...
The dirty stage is over.
I found several dead birds at the back of the flue; all dried out :(
Ready for the plastering next week
Excited about the little nook on the side
Insert the new closet here (it's not like we've already started drawing it 🙈)
Oh, look what we found behind the radiator!
And we even thought to add a lovely little ventilation grille to prevent the chimney from taking in moisture
The chimney sweep has installed the hat and the wind deflector. This should be a bit safer for the crows that nest up there 🪦
The plasterer is done. We'll install the floor tomorrow!
The cork underlayer is laid, I improvised a wood dust extractor using a roll of toilet paper as an accessory for the vacuum cleaner 😂
A portion of the planks has been sorted and is ready to be laid. Just taking a tea break
Well, progress has been slow today due to very delicate cuts around the door frames to achieve a smooth transition into the hallway (which is also being laid). @user45@twitter.com has cursed me
Finished, but on hinges! Finishing touch: incomprehensible instructions for assembling the new bed. We'll sleep well tonight!
To do: the hallway floor, all the baseboards. The decorator is coming in a month, so for now at home it's bare plaster wall chic
A little evening DIY session to remove the lower sections of the door frames with a miter saw or coping saw where we want the floor to fit perfectly.
The underlay of the hallway is also laid
We finished the hallway floor yesterday! Then left at 5 AM this morning to pick up Thing 1 from Heathrow, then a nap and finishing up the hallway; baseboards installed. We'll take care of the sealing when the glue has set.
